  "body": "After upgrading to 0.8.0-rc2, the app was working just fine.\r\nThen I've received a new community invite from @iurimatias .\r\n\r\nI requested access to that community.\r\nFirst bug: the community view still said \"Request to jion\", even though I did send a request already.\r\n\r\nBecause this was the case, I've restarted the app.\r\nAfter restart, the app is now reproducibly crashing with\r\n\r\n```\r\nTraceback (most recent call last)\r\n/home/rabbit/projects/status-im/status-desktop/src/nim_status_client.nim(181) nim_status_client \r\n/home/rabbit/projects/status-im/status-desktop/src/nim_status_client.nim(178) mainProc\r\n/home/rabbit/projects/status-im/status-desktop/vendor/nimqml/src/nimqml/private/qguiapplication.nim(29) exec\r\n/home/rabbit/projects/status-im/status-desktop/vendor/nimqml/src/nimqml/private/qobject.nim(49) qobjectCallback\r\n/home/rabbit/projects/status-im/status-desktop/vendor/nimqml/src/nimqml/private/qobject.nim(34) onSlotCalled\r\n/home/rabbit/projects/status-im/status-desktop/vendor/nimbus-build-system/vendor/Nim/lib/core/macros.nim(566) onSlotCalled\r\n/home/rabbit/projects/status-im/status-desktop/src/app/core/signals/signals_manager.nim(56) receiveSignal\r\n/home/rabbit/projects/status-im/status-desktop/src/app/core/signals/signals_manager.nim(53) processSignal\r\n/home/rabbit/projects/status-im/status-desktop/src/app/core/eventemitter.nim(57) emit\r\n/home/rabbit/projects/status-im/status-desktop/src/app_service/service/contacts/service.nim(164) :anonymous\r\n/home/rabbit/projects/status-im/status-desktop/src/app_service/service/contacts/service.nim(158) updateAndEmitStatuses\r\n/home/rabbit/projects/status-im/status-desktop/src/app/core/eventemitter.nim(57) emit\r\n/home/rabbit/projects/status-im/status-desktop/src/app/modules/main/controller.nim(200) :anonymous\r\n/home/rabbit/projects/status-im/status-desktop/src/app/modules/main/io_interface.nim(123) contactsStatusUpdated\r\n/home/rabbit/projects/status-im/status-desktop/src/app/modules/main/module.nim(824) contactsStatusUpdated\r\n/home/rabbit/projects/status-im/status-desktop/src/app/modules/shared_models/active_section.nim(226) setOnlineStatusForMember\r\n/home/rabbit/projects/status-im/status-desktop/src/app/modules/shared_models/section_item.nim(264) setOnlineStatusForMember\r\n/home/rabbit/projects/status-im/status-desktop/src/app/modules/shared_models/member_model.nim(281) setOnlineStatus\r\n/home/rabbit/projects/status-im/status-desktop/src/app/modules/shared_models/member_model.nim(154) findIndexForMember\r\nSIGSEGV: Illegal storage access. (Attempt to read from nil?)\r\nDBG 2022-11-21 16:38:46.614+01:00 NewBE_callPrivateRPC                       topics=\"rpc\" tid=384873 file=core.nim:20 rpc_method=wallet_fetchTokenDetails\r\nmake: *** [Makefile:631: run-linux] Error 1\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe problem is that `SIGSEGV: Illegal storage access. (Attempt to read from nil?)` could literally happen anywhere.\r\nSo this is very hard to debug.\r\n\r\nI've backed up the Status folder of this state so it can be looked into.\r\n\r\n",
